      • addTime

        public static java.lang.String addTime(java.lang.String reserveStartTime,
                                       int hourIncrement)
        This method is used to add an hour increment to a starting time probably in the most complicated way. This is used for student/user reservations where reservations can only be made for one day.
        Parameters:
        reserveStartTime - start time
        hourIncrement - the number to add to the start time
        Returns:
        endTime the result of adding the hour increment and the time

      • subtractTime

        public static java.lang.String subtractTime(java.lang.String time,
                                            int hourIncrement)
        This method will subtract the hours of a start time by the reservation length (hour) For example, 23:00:00 - 2 = 21:00:00 This method subtracts the hour only.
        Parameters:
        time - String time in HH:mm:ss (24-hour) SQL format
        hourIncrement - Integer reservation length
        Returns:
        The difference from of the start time - reservation length (hour increment)
